core\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is when you can see him, and Team SA, in action.\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 382, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5731314533006736e-36, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa remain somewhat stranded on four medals at the Olympiccs, with a few near-misses in recent days, but there will be an enduring hope that Wayde van Niekerk can wind back the clock to achieve something special on the track.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 4.259493208139751e-12, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 548, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will not be running in the 400m - where he famously won gold in 2016 - but hisattention has turned solely to the 200m race.\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 32-year-old veteran will be in action at 19:55 in his highly-anticipated heat on Monday night.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is more athletics and 'sport climbing'on the menu for Team SA.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5731314533006736e-36, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ATHLETICS  Men's discus qualification, Group A (10.10am):Francois Prinsloo  Men's discus qualification, Group A (11.35am):Victor Hogan  Women's 400m heats (12.35pm):Miranda Coetzee  Women's 800m final (9.45pm):Prudence Sekgodiso  Men's 200m heats (7.55pm):Wayde van Niekerk  Men's 200m heats (8.09pm):Benjamin Richardson  Men's 200m heats (8.23pm):Shaun Maswangani  SPORT CLIMBING  Men's boulder & lead, semi-final boulder (10am):Mel Janse van Rensburg  Women's speed qualification seeding heats (1pm):Aniya Holder  ATHLETICS  Women's 800m, semi-finals:Prudence Sekgodiso finished 2nd in her semi-final in 1:57.57 to qualify for the final  Men's 100m, semi-finals:Shaun Maswanganyi finished 5th in his race in\\u00a0 a season's best 10.02 but did not progress to the final  Men's 100m, final:Akani Simbine finished 4th in 9.82sec  Men's 100m, semi-finals:Akani Simbine won his heat in 9.87 and progressed to the final  Men's 100m, semi-finals:Benjamin Richardson finished 3rd in his semi-final in 9.95, just missing out on a place in the final  Men's 400m, round 1 heats:Lythe Pillay finished 6th in his heat in 45.60 and progressed to the repechage stage  Men's 400m, round 1 heats:Zakhiti Nene finished 4th in 45.01 and progressed to the repechage stage  Men's long jump qualification, Group A:Jovan van Vuuren produced a best leap of 7.70m which left him in 23rd spot overall and missing out on the top 12 for the final  Men's long jump qualification, Group B:Cheswill Johnson produced a best leap of 4.49m which left him in 31st spot overall and missing out on the top 12 for the final  Women's 400m H, first round, heats:Rogail Joseph produced a personal best 54.56sec to finish 2nd in her heat and automatically qualify for the semi-finals  Women's 400m H, first round, heats:Zeney Geldenhuys finished 3rd in her heat to qualify automatically for the semi-finals  CYCLING  Women's road race:Ashleigh Moolman Pasio finished 33rd in 4hr 4min 23sec, exactly 5:00 behind gold medallist Kristen Faulkner of the USA.\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 2941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1035, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.1007752268752364e-12, \"text\": \"Group A\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_A\"}, {\"begin\": 1053, \"end\": 1065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hogan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Hogan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hogan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hogan\"}, {\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Coetzee\", \"score\": 0.9999999942469913, \"rank\": 3.3418679316959132e-09, \"text\": \"Coetzee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Coetzee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Coetzee\"}, {\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.999045186427857, \"rank\": 0.0009091586281432956, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999973928363368, \"rank\": 2.606976482213612e-06, \"text\": \"Richardson\", 